==Abstract==

This IIP describes using DNS TXT records to publish payment instructions. It implements BIP 353 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Human-readable payment identifiers (user@domain.com) are easier to share than addresses. DNS provides:
* Familiar format
* Decentralized infrastructure
* DNSSEC authentication

==Specification==

===DNS Record Format===

TXT record at: _intcoin-payment.<user>._intcoin.<domain>

<pre>
intcoin:int1q...?label=Donation
</pre>

===Lookup Process===

For payment to user@domain.com:
# Query TXT record: _intcoin-payment.user._intcoin.domain.com
# Parse URI from response
# Optionally verify DNSSEC signatures

===URI Format===

Standard IIP-23 URI format:
<pre>
intcoin:<address>[?amount=<amount>][&label=<label>]
</pre>

===DNSSEC===

DNSSEC verification is RECOMMENDED:
* Prevents DNS spoofing attacks
* Provides authentication of payment instructions

===Multiple Records===

Multiple TXT records MAY be present for:
* Different amounts/purposes
* Fallback addresses

===Example===

DNS record for donations@example.com:
<pre>
_intcoin-payment.donations._intcoin.example.com. IN TXT "intcoin:int1qr7vy6sqrl8y22zl6rzw59v07e6r3k9unuwe3r9v2snz30swzaqw7wwd24y?label=Donations"
</pre>

